text: Moses Henry Cass (18 February 1927 – 26 February 2022) was an Australian doctor and politician. He was Minister for Environment and Conservation (1972–1975), the Environment (1975), and the Media (1975) during the Gough Whitlam government. He represented the Division of Maribyrnong in the House of Representatives from 1969 to 1983. Cass died on 26 February 2022 at the age of 95. ==References== Category:1927 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Australian Labor Party politicians Category:Politicians from Western Australia Category:Politicians from Melbourne
